OL,3,CRugby league great mic'd up for new
OL,4,Cdocumentary
OL,6,F"I've been able to play for my
OL,7,Fhometown club, go and live in New
OL,8,FZealand and play there, and in France
OL,9,Ffor the last five years so I've ticked
OL,10,Fa lot of boxes, but it was tough to
OL,11,Fget over that last defeat."
OL,13,FSam admits he would still love to be
OL,14,Fplaying, but it was a knee injury
OL,15,Fwhich forced him into retirement.
OL,17,FHe said: "I'm 34-years-old, I've been
OL,18,Fplaying since I was 17. It was
OL,19,Finevitable at some point something
OL,20,Fwould stop me."
